53template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(short i)
54 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
55{
56 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
57 m_value.num = static_cast<double>(i);
58}
59
60template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator short() const
61{
62 if (primitiveUnitType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER)
63 return clampTo<short>(m_value.num);
64
65 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
66 return 0;
67}
68
69template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(unsigned short i)
70 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
71{
72 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
73 m_value.num = static_cast<double>(i);
74}
75
76template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator unsigned short() const
77{
78 if (primitiveType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER)
79 return value<unsigned short>();
80
81 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
82 return 0;
83}

85template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator int() const
86{
87 if (primitiveType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER)
88 return value<int>();
89
90 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
91 return 0;
92}

94template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator unsigned() const

96 if (primitiveType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER)

99 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
100 return 0;

111template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator float() const

120template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(LineClampValue i)
121 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
122{
123 setPrimitiveUnitType(i.isPercentage() ? CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE : CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
124 m_value.num = static_cast<double>(i.value());
125}
126
127template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator LineClampValue() const
128{
129 if (primitiveType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER)
130 return LineClampValue(value<int>(), LineClamp::LineCount);
131
132 if (primitiveType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE)
133 return LineClampValue(value<int>(), LineClamp::Percentage);
134
135 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
136 return LineClampValue();
137}
138
139template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(ReflectionDirection direction)
140 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
141{
142 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
143 switch (direction) {
144 case ReflectionDirection::Above:
145 m_value.valueID = CSSValueAbove;
146 break;
147 case ReflectionDirection::Below:
148 m_value.valueID = CSSValueBelow;
149 break;
150 case ReflectionDirection::Left:
151 m_value.valueID = CSSValueLeft;
152 break;
153 case ReflectionDirection::Right:
154 m_value.valueID = CSSValueRight;
155 }
156}
157
158template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator ReflectionDirection() const
159{
160 ASSERT(isValueID());
161
162 switch (m_value.valueID) {
163 case CSSValueAbove:
164 return ReflectionDirection::Above;
165 case CSSValueBelow:
166 return ReflectionDirection::Below;
167 case CSSValueLeft:
168 return ReflectionDirection::Left;
169 case CSSValueRight:
170 return ReflectionDirection::Right;
171 default:
172 break;
173 }
174
175 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
176 return ReflectionDirection::Below;
177}
178
179template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(ColumnFill columnFill)
180 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
181{
182 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
183 switch (columnFill) {
184 case ColumnFill::Auto:
185 m_value.valueID = CSSValueAuto;
186 break;
187 case ColumnFill::Balance:
188 m_value.valueID = CSSValueBalance;
189 break;
190 }
191}
192
193template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator ColumnFill() const
194{
195 if (primitiveUnitType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID) {
196 if (m_value.valueID == CSSValueBalance)
197 return ColumnFill::Balance;
198 if (m_value.valueID == CSSValueAuto)
199 return ColumnFill::Auto;
200 }
201 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
202 return ColumnFill::Balance;
203}
204
205template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(ColumnSpan columnSpan)
206 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
207{
208 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
209 switch (columnSpan) {
210 case ColumnSpan::All:
211 m_value.valueID = CSSValueAll;
212 break;
213 case ColumnSpan::None:
214 m_value.valueID = CSSValueNone;
215 break;
216 }
217}
218
219template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator ColumnSpan() const
220{
221 // Map 1 to none for compatibility reasons.
222 if (primitiveUnitType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER && m_value.num == 1)
223 return ColumnSpan::None;
224
225 ASSERT(isValueID());
226
227 switch (m_value.valueID) {
228 case CSSValueAll:
229 return ColumnSpan::All;
230 case CSSValueNone:
231 return ColumnSpan::None;
232 default:
233 break;
234 }
235
236 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
237 return ColumnSpan::None;
238}

250 m_value.valueID = CSSValueEconomy;
251 break;
252 }
253}

255template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator PrintColorAdjust() const
256{
257 ASSERT(isValueID());
258
259 switch (m_value.valueID) {
260 case CSSValueEconomy:
261 return PrintColorAdjust::Economy;
262 case CSSValueExact:
263 return PrintColorAdjust::Exact;
264 default:
265 break;
266 }
267
268 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
269 return PrintColorAdjust::Economy;
270}

273template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(BorderStyle e)
274 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
275{
276 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
277 switch (e) {
278 case BorderStyle::None:
279 m_value.valueID = CSSValueNone;
280 break;
281 case BorderStyle::Hidden:
282 m_value.valueID = CSSValueHidden;
283 break;
284 case BorderStyle::Inset:
285 m_value.valueID = CSSValueInset;
286 break;
287 case BorderStyle::Groove:
288 m_value.valueID = CSSValueGroove;
289 break;
290 case BorderStyle::Ridge:
291 m_value.valueID = CSSValueRidge;
292 break;
293 case BorderStyle::Outset:
294 m_value.valueID = CSSValueOutset;
295 break;
296 case BorderStyle::Dotted:
297 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDotted;
298 break;
299 case BorderStyle::Dashed:
300 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDashed;
301 break;
302 case BorderStyle::Solid:
303 m_value.valueID = CSSValueSolid;
304 break;
305 case BorderStyle::Double:
306 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDouble;
307 break;
308 }
309}
310
311template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator BorderStyle() const
312{
313 ASSERT(isValueID());
314
315 if (m_value.valueID == CSSValueAuto) // Valid for CSS outline-style
316 return BorderStyle::Dotted;
317 return static_cast<BorderStyle>(m_value.valueID - CSSValueNone);
318}
319
320template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator OutlineIsAuto() const
321{
322 ASSERT(isValueID());
323
324 if (m_value.valueID == CSSValueAuto)
325 return OutlineIsAuto::On;
326 return OutlineIsAuto::Off;
327}

329template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(CompositeOperator e)
330 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
331{
332 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
333 switch (e) {
334 case CompositeOperator::Clear:
335 m_value.valueID = CSSValueClear;
336 break;
337 case CompositeOperator::Copy:
338 m_value.valueID = CSSValueCopy;
339 break;
340 case CompositeOperator::SourceOver:
341 m_value.valueID = CSSValueSourceOver;
342 break;
343 case CompositeOperator::SourceIn:
344 m_value.valueID = CSSValueSourceIn;
345 break;
346 case CompositeOperator::SourceOut:
347 m_value.valueID = CSSValueSourceOut;
348 break;
349 case CompositeOperator::SourceAtop:
350 m_value.valueID = CSSValueSourceAtop;
351 break;
352 case CompositeOperator::DestinationOver:
353 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDestinationOver;
354 break;
355 case CompositeOperator::DestinationIn:
356 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDestinationIn;
357 break;
358 case CompositeOperator::DestinationOut:
359 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDestinationOut;
360 break;
361 case CompositeOperator::DestinationAtop:
362 m_value.valueID = CSSValueDestinationAtop;
363 break;
364 case CompositeOperator::XOR:
365 m_value.valueID = CSSValueXor;
366 break;
367 case CompositeOperator::PlusDarker:
368 m_value.valueID = CSSValuePlusDarker;
369 break;
370 case CompositeOperator::PlusLighter:
371 m_value.valueID = CSSValuePlusLighter;
372 break;
373 case CompositeOperator::Difference:
374 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
375 break;
376 }
377}
378
379template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator CompositeOperator() const
380{
381 ASSERT(isValueID());
382
383 switch (m_value.valueID) {
384 case CSSValueClear:
385 return CompositeOperator::Clear;
386 case CSSValueCopy:
387 return CompositeOperator::Copy;
388 case CSSValueSourceOver:
389 return CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
390 case CSSValueSourceIn:
391 return CompositeOperator::SourceIn;
392 case CSSValueSourceOut:
393 return CompositeOperator::SourceOut;
394 case CSSValueSourceAtop:
395 return CompositeOperator::SourceAtop;
396 case CSSValueDestinationOver:
397 return CompositeOperator::DestinationOver;
398 case CSSValueDestinationIn:
399 return CompositeOperator::DestinationIn;
400 case CSSValueDestinationOut:
401 return CompositeOperator::DestinationOut;
402 case CSSValueDestinationAtop:
403 return CompositeOperator::DestinationAtop;
404 case CSSValueXor:
405 return CompositeOperator::XOR;
406 case CSSValuePlusDarker:
407 return CompositeOperator::PlusDarker;
408 case CSSValuePlusLighter:
409 return CompositeOperator::PlusLighter;
410 default:
411 break;
412 }
413
414 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
415 return CompositeOperator::Clear;
416}

626template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator ControlPart() const
627{
628 ASSERT(isValueID());
629
630 if (m_value.valueID == CSSValueNone)
631 return NoControlPart;
632 return ControlPart(m_value.valueID - CSSValueCheckbox + 1);
633}

635template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(BackfaceVisibility e)
636 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
637{
638 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
639 switch (e) {
640 case BackfaceVisibility::Visible:
641 m_value.valueID = CSSValueVisible;
642 break;
643 case BackfaceVisibility::Hidden:
644 m_value.valueID = CSSValueHidden;
645 break;
646 }
647}
648
649template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator BackfaceVisibility() const
650{
651 ASSERT(isValueID());
652
653 switch (m_value.valueID) {
654 case CSSValueVisible:
655 return BackfaceVisibility::Visible;
656 case CSSValueHidden:
657 return BackfaceVisibility::Hidden;
658 default:
659 break;
660 }
661
662 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
663 return BackfaceVisibility::Hidden;
664}

703template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(FillBox e)

710 break;
711 case FillBox::Padding:

713 break;
714 case FillBox::Content:

723template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator FillBox() const
724{
725 ASSERT(isValueID());
726
727 switch (m_value.valueID) {
728 case CSSValueBorder:
729 case CSSValueBorderBox:
730 return FillBox::Border;
731 case CSSValuePadding:
732 case CSSValuePaddingBox:
733 return FillBox::Padding;
734 case CSSValueContent:
735 case CSSValueContentBox:
736 return FillBox::Content;
737 case CSSValueText:
738 case CSSValueWebkitText:
739 return FillBox::Text;
740 default:
741 break;
742 }
743
744 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
745 return FillBox::Border;
746}

789template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(BoxPack e)
790 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
791{
792 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);
793 switch (e) {
794 case BoxPack::Start:
795 m_value.valueID = CSSValueStart;
796 break;
797 case BoxPack::Center:
798 m_value.valueID = CSSValueCenter;
799 break;
800 case BoxPack::End:
801 m_value.valueID = CSSValueEnd;
802 break;
803 case BoxPack::Justify:
804 m_value.valueID = CSSValueJustify;
805 break;
806 }
807}

809template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::operator BoxPack() const
810{
811 ASSERT(isValueID());
812
813 switch (m_value.valueID) {
814 case CSSValueStart:
815 return BoxPack::Start;
816 case CSSValueEnd:
817 return BoxPack::End;
818 case CSSValueCenter:
819 return BoxPack::Center;
820 case CSSValueJustify:
821 return BoxPack::Justify;
822 default:
823 break;
824 }
825
826 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
827 return BoxPack::Justify;
828}

830template<> inline CSSPrimitiveValue::CSSPrimitiveValue(BoxAlignment e)
831 : CSSValue(PrimitiveClass)
832{
833 setPrimitiveUnitType(CSSUnitType::CSS_VALUE_ID);

1672 }

1674 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1675 return OptionSet<HangingPunctuation> { };

1734inline CSSValueID toCSSValueID(ListStyleType style)
1735{
1736 switch (style) {
1737 case ListStyleType::None:
1738 return CSSValueNone;
1739 case ListStyleType::String:
1740 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1741 return CSSValueInvalid;
1742 default:
1743 return static_cast<CSSValueID>(static_cast<int>(CSSValueDisc) + static_cast<uint8_t>(style));
1744 }
1745}

4320
4321enum LengthConversion {
4322 AnyConversion = ~0,
4323 FixedIntegerConversion = 1 << 0,
4324 FixedFloatConversion = 1 << 1,
4325 AutoConversion = 1 << 2,
4326 PercentConversion = 1 << 3,
4327 CalculatedConversion = 1 << 4
4328};
4329
4330inline bool CSSPrimitiveValue::convertingToLengthRequiresNonNullStyle(int lengthConversion) const
4331{
4332 ASSERT(isFontRelativeLength());
4333 // This matches the implementation in CSSPrimitiveValue::computeLengthDouble().
4334 switch (primitiveUnitType()) {
4335 case CSSUnitType::CSS_EMS:
4336 case CSSUnitType::CSS_EXS:
4337 case CSSUnitType::CSS_CHS:
4338 case CSSUnitType::CSS_LHS:
4339 return lengthConversion & (FixedIntegerConversion | FixedFloatConversion);
4340 default:
4341 return false;
4342 }
4343}
4344
4345template<int supported> Length CSSPrimitiveValue::convertToLength(const CSSToLengthConversionData& conversionData) const
4346{
4347 if (isFontRelativeLength() && convertingToLengthRequiresNonNullStyle(supported) && !conversionData.style())
4348 return Length(LengthType::Undefined);
4349 if ((supported & FixedIntegerConversion) && isLength())
4350 return computeLength<Length>(conversionData);
4351 if ((supported & FixedFloatConversion) && isLength())
4352 return Length(computeLength<double>(conversionData), LengthType::Fixed);
4353 if ((supported & PercentConversion) && isPercentage())
4354 return Length(doubleValue(), LengthType::Percent);
4355 if ((supported & AutoConversion) && valueID() == CSSValueAuto)
4356 return Length(LengthType::Auto);
4357 if ((supported & CalculatedConversion) && isCalculated())
4358 return Length(cssCalcValue()->createCalculationValue(conversionData));
4359 return Length(LengthType::Undefined);
4360}
